message: Focus on cooking raw ingredients with the stove first, as this generally increases their base value. Combine 2-3 cooked ingredients that are culinarily logical together to make a valuable dish. Be very cautious about combining 4 or more items into a single dish, as this frequently leads to 'overcomplicated' items with significantly negative values. The 'water' tool seemed to decrease item values in my experience, so use it sparingly or only when other options are exhausted. Once you have a high-value item (around 80), it's often safest to submit rather than risk a negative outcome by trying to combine further.

Be cautious when cooking grains, as they often don't add value or can lead to negative values. The optimal strategy seems to be cooking individual protein and vegetable ingredients and then combining them.
